Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt with St. Joseph sleeping at left, in a hexagonal frame; copy in reverse Etching
Curator's comments: Although this copy attributes the invention of the composition to Guido Reni, no similar works are known by him. For an original print by Cantarini see: U,3.63.
Bibliographic references: Bartsch / Le Peintre graveur (XIX.126.7) (copy in reverse)
Massari 1997 / In 'Simone Cantarini detto il Pesarese', ed. Andrea Emiliani (31) (copy in reverse)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (with Philipe's blindstamp and initials CMC)
